%222052%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Apple%20CEO%20Steve%20Jobs%20shows%20off%20the%20first%20iPhone%20on%20stage%20at%20an%20Apple%20event%20with%20the%20Apple%20logo%20looming%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d8986dcdb354a9855f8dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221588%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteve%20Jobs%20unveiled%20the%20first%20iPhone%20in%202007.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Sakuma%2F%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202007%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20unveiled%20the%20original%20iPhone%20onstage%20at%20a%20Macworld%20Expo%2C%20the%20device%20has%20become%20Apple's%20biggest%20moneymaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20quarter%2C%20Apple%20generated%20almost%20%2470%20billion%20of%20its%20%24119.6%20billion%20total%20revenue%20from%20iPhone%20sales.%20That%20was%20up%20from%20%2465.8%20billion%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20showing%20growth%20is%20still%20happening%20in%20its%20most%20important%20product%20segment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20growth%20isn't%20exactly%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20Apple's%20most%20important%20international%20market%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-to-face-huge-threat-to-iphone-in-china-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20started%20to%20sour%20on%20iPhones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bucking%20a%20trend%20of%20growth%20in%20other%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20shared%20signs%20of%20this%20trend%20starting%20to%20form%20in%20the%20last%20three%20months%20of%202023%20as%20net%20sales%20in%20the%20Greater%20China%20region%20fell%20almost%2013%25%20from%20%2423.9%20billion%20in%202022%20to%20%2420.8%20billion.%20That%20hasn't%20changed%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EiPhone%20sales%20in%20China%20dropped%2024%25%20in%20the%20first%20six%20weeks%20of%20the%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-sales-china-down-huawei-vivo-smartphone-2024-3%23%3A~%3Atext%3DApple%2520is%2520no%2520longer%2520the%2CVivo%252C%2520Huawei%252C%2520and%2520Honor.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20data%20from%20Counterpoint%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20has%20led%20Apple%20to%20slip%20to%20fourth%20spot%20in%20smartphone%20market%20share%2C%20behind%20local%20rivals%20Vivo%2C%20Huawei%2C%20and%20Honor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20is%20Apple%20sliding%20in%20China%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20key%20reasons%20for%20this.%20For%20one%2C%20Beijing%20has%20made%20it%20less%20appealing%20to%20buy%20iPhones.%20It%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-bans-iphone-use-for-government-officials-at-work-635fe2f8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20by%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20had%20banned%20officials%20from%20using%20iPhones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWill%20Wong%2C%20a%20Singapore-based%20senior%20research%20manager%20with%20IDC's%20Asia%2FPacific%20Client%20Devices%20Group%2C%20said%20a%20soft%20Chinese%20economy%20has%20led%20to%20more%20cautious%20consumer%20spending%20at%20large.%20He%20also%20pointed%20to%20a%20shift%20in%20consumer%20preferences%20in%20China%20as%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20Apple%20has%20lost%20its%20top%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20important%20reason%20is%20that%20the%20local%20consumers%20have%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Wong%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20FOMO%20sentiment%20is%20not%20as%20strong%20as%20before%20and%20the%20youngsters%20are%20also%20embracing%20the%20so-called%20'B1B2%20economy.'%26quot%3B%20The%20B1B2%20economy%20refers%20to%20a%20trend%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F12%2F06%2Fchinas-youths-shop-at-b1b2-bargain-basements-as-economy-bites.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20youths%20shopping%20in%20the%20basement%20levels%20of%20malls%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20stores%20on%20lower%20floors%20tend%20to%20carry%20lower-cost%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EViable%20homegrown%20competition%20has%20emerged%2C%20too.%20Huawei%20released%20a%205G%20smartphone%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhuawei-smartphone-own-designs-processors-5g-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMate%2060%20Pro%20%3C%2Fa%3Elast%20year%20that%20was%20championed%20at%20home%20thanks%20to%20its%20use%20of%20domestic%20chips.%20Unit%20sales%20of%20Huawei%20phones%20jumped%2064%25%20in%20the%20first%20six%20weeks%20of%20the%20year%2C%20per%20Counterpoint%20Research.%20Huawei%20had%20to%20increase%20production%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Ftech%2Fbig-tech%2Farticle%2F3241541%2Fhuawei-has-big-problem-popular-mate-60-5g-smartphones-theres-not-enough-supply-meet-growing-demand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekeep%20up%20with%20the%20demand%20for%20the%20phone%20after%20its%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20wait%20time%20for%20the%20phone%20extending%20up%20to%20three%20months%20by%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAndroid%20vendors%20have%20been%20promoting%20foldable%20and%20AI%2C%20while%20Apple%20brought%20little%20excitement%20to%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20Wong%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20customer%20tries%20out%20Huawei%20Mate%2060%20smartphone%20at%20a%20Huawei%20flagship%20store%20on%20September%204%2C%202023%20in%20Shanghai%2C%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fea036a39a1b00190cd7e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Huawei%20Mate%2060%20rivals%20the%20latest%20iPhone.%3Cp%3EWang%20Gang%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGene%20Munster%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20and%20cofounder%20at%20Deepwater%20Asset%20Management%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20demand%20for%20the%20iPhone%20in%20China%20follows%20a%20boom-bust%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Apple%20has%20a%20strong%20upgrade%20cycle%20one%20year%20it's%20followed%20by%20softer%20demand%20in%20year%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20Munster%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20suspect%20demand%20next%20year%20will%20see%20a%20rebound.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunster%20added%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bmovement%20for%20made-in-China%20from%20Chinese%20consumers%26quot%3B%20also%20contributes%20to%20Apple's%20soft%20sales%20in%202024%20so%20far%2C%20though%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent%20than%20the%20boom-bust%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Apple%20can%20rely%20on%20other%20regions%20to%20continue%20to%20snap%20up%20iterative%20upgrades%20to%20its%20iPhone%2C%20the%20threat%20of%20Chinese%20consumers%20abandoning%20its%20phones%20in%20favor%20of%20homegrown%20ones%20is%20a%20problem.%20Especially%20so%20as%20they%20represent%20close%20to%20a%20fifth%20of%20Apple's%20revenue%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Ives%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Wedbush%2C%20said%20slipping%20iPhone%2015%20sales%20matched%20with%20additional%20discounting%20on%20the%20device%20had%20given%20investors%20%26quot%3Bagita.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20cherry%20on%20top%20of%20the%20sundae%20of%20bad%20news%20from%20Cupertino%20with%20last%20week's%20reports%20that%20Apple%20is%20ditching%20the%20EV%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%20for%20Apple%2C%20it%20is%20working%20on%20something%20this%20year%20that%20could%20give%20the%20iPhone%20the%20much-needed%20upgrade%20it's%20seeking%3A%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-tim-cook-finally-ready-to-talk-about-ai-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECook%20shared%20that%20Apple%20would%20be%20ready%20to%20share%20details%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20its%20work%20on%20AI%20later%20this%20