nd%20Marco%20Polo%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%208.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-8-the-vijayanagar-empire%5C%22%3EThe%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mughal%20Empire%20was%20founded%20in%201526%20by%20Babur%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20a%20long%20line%20of%20people%20%E2%80%93%20since%20at%20least%20the%20Indo-Aryans%20%E2%80%93%20to%20have%20entered%20and%20settled%20in%20the%20subcontinent.%20It%20grew%20to%20become%20the%20largest%2C%20most%20opulent%20empire%20yet%20in%20India.%20As%20with%20most%20long-lasting%2C%20multi-ethnic%2C%20and%20multilingual%20empires%2C%20most%20Mughal%20rulers%20too%20espoused%20pragmatic%20ideals%2C%20especially%20Akbar%20and%20Jahangir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECo-opting%20elites%20from%20diverse%20groups%20of%20Hindus%20into%20their%20administration%2C%20they%20presided%20over%20a%20brilliant%20fusion%20of%20Indo-Persian%20culture%20and%20syncretic%20creations%20in%20art%2C%20architecture%2C%20literature%2C%20music%2C%20dance%2C%20painting%2C%20cuisine%2C%20dress%2C%20crafts%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201658%2C%20a%20French%20doctor%2C%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Bernier%2C%20came%20to%20Delhi%20as%20a%20physician%20to%20Dara%20Shikoh%2C%20and%20wrote%20about%20the%20bloody%20war%20of%20royal%20succession%20and%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20Bernier%E2%80%99s%20insightful%20account%20describes%20Mughal%20courtly%20culture%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20economic%20condition%20of%20Indians%2C%20their%20science%20and%20intellectual%20life%2C%20and%20Hindu%20cultural%20and%20religious%20customs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholars%20routinely%20critique%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%E2%80%99s%20record%20on%20many%20fronts%2C%20but%20the%20Mughals%20have%20lately%20also%20attracted%20much%20cultural%20vilification%2C%20especially%20from%20Hindu%20nationalists.%20They%20allege%20that%20the%20Mughals%20persecuted%20and%20forcibly%20converted%20Hindus%20to%20Islam%20on%20a%20large%20scale%2C%20and%20indiscriminately%20desecrated%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20true%3F%20I%E2%80%99ll%20explore%20the%20evidence%20behind%20such%20allegations%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20lot%20more%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FmJ5R33p67RA%3Fsi%3DSelciCHjYgOdneXG%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20the%20full%20transcript%20of%20the%20episode.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20Indians.%20I%E2%80%99m%20Namit%20Arora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20episode%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%2C%20and%20the%20secrets%20of%20its%20wealth%20and%20military%20power%20that%20foreign%20travellers%20wrote%20about.%20As%20Vijayanagar%20declined%20in%20the%2016th%20century%20south%20India%2C%20a%20new%20power%20was%20rising%20in%20north%20India%3A%20The%20Mughal%20Empire.%20It%20would%20become%20the%20largest%20empire%20India%20had%20ever%20known%E2%80%94unmatched%20in%20its%20reach%20and%20opulence.%20It%20would%20produce%20an%20extraordinary%20fusion%20of%20Indo-Persian%20culture%20and%20syncretic%20creations%20in%20art%2C%20architecture%2C%20literature%2C%20music%2C%20dance%2C%20painting%2C%20cuisine%2C%20dress%2C%20crafts%2C%20and%20more.%20Emperors%20like%20Babur%2C%20Humayun%2C%20Akbar%2C%20Jahangir%2C%20Shah%20Jahan%2C%20and%20Aurangzeb%20would%20inspire%20many%20a%20Bollywood%20epic%20and%2C%20lately%2C%20a%20host%20of%20funny%20Internet%20memes.%20But%20for%20many%20Hindu%20nationalists%2C%20this%20is%20no%20laughing%20matter.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20come%20to%20despise%20the%20Mughals%2C%20largely%20led%20by%20their%20chauvinistic%20ideology%20and%20gross%20exaggerations%20about%20forced%20religious%20conversions%20and%20temple%20desecrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20episode%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20look%20at%20Mughal%20India%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20time%20of%20Aurangzeb%20(1658%E2%80%931707)%2C%20perhaps%20the%20most%20controversial%20of%20the%20Mughals.%20Among%20other%20sources%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20lean%20on%20the%20amazing%20account%20of%20a%20French%20doctor%2C%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Bernier%2C%20who%20spent%2012%20years%20in%20India%20(1658%E2%80%9369)%20working%20with%20one%20of%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20ministers%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mughal%20Empire%20was%20founded%20by%20Babur%20(1483%E2%80%931530).%20His%20ancestors%20were%20Turks%20and%20Mongols%2C%20and%20included%20both%20Genghis%20Khan%20and%20Tamerlane%E2%80%94a%20rather%20distinguished%20lineage%2C%20as%20these%20things%20go.%20His%20father%20had%20ruled%20a%20small%20kingdom%20in%20Uzbekistan%2C%20which%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Persian%20cultural%20zone.%20Babur%20was%20only%2011%20years%20old%20when%20his%20father%20died.%20For%20the%20next%20two%20decades%2C%20he%20and%20his%20family%20struggled%20to%20keep%20and%20expand%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20kingdom%2C%20but%20without%20much%20success.%20In%20his%2030s%2C%20Babur%20began%20looking%20for%20new%20territories%2C%20and%20set%20his%20sights%20on%20the%20land%20beyond%20the%20Sindhu%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Hindustan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201526%2C%20Babur%20challenged%20Ibrahim%20Lodi%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Sultanate.%20With%20just%208%2C000%20troops%2C%20he%20defeated%20Lodi%20at%20the%20battle%20of%20Panipat%2C%20took%20over%20his%20new%20capital%20at%20Agra%2C%20and%20launched%20the%20Mughal%20Empire.%20Babur%20died%20just%20four%20years%20later%2C%20but%20he%20left%20behind%20a%20thoughtful%20memoir%20of%20his%20life%2C%20Baburnama%2C%20in%20which%20he%20also%20observed%20that%20Hindustan%20had%20%E2%80%98no%20good%20horses%2C%20no%20good%20dogs%2C%20no%20grapes%2C%20musk-melons%20or%20first-rate%20fruits%2C%20no%20ice%2C%20no%20good%20bread%20or%20cooked%20food%20in%20the%20bazaars%2C%20no%20hot-baths%2C%20no%20colleges%2C%20%5Band%5D%20no%20candles.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBabur%20was%20another%20in%20a%20long%20line%20of%20outsiders%2C%20since%20at%20least%20the%20Indo-Aryans%2C%20who%20had%20come%20to%20settle%20in%20India.%20Others%20before%20him%20include%20the%20Scythians%2C%20Kushans%2C%20Ahiras%2C%20Huns%2C%20Tibeto-Burmans.%20From%20the%2012th%20century%2C%20new%20groups%20began%20entering%20India%20from%20the%20northwest%E2%80%94Turks%2C%20Persians%2C%20Arabs%2C%20Afghans%2C%20Uzbeks%2C%20and%20others.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20these%20newest%20outsiders%20resembled%20the%20Indo-Aryans%2C%20especially%20in%20their%20genetic%20ancestry%20and%20their%20aggressive%2C%20patriarchal%20ways.%20Their%20different%20cultures%20and%20identities%20would%20also%20become%20fresh%20sources%20of%20both%20conflict%20and%20creativity%20in%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAkbar%20the%20Great%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBabur%E2%80%99s%20grandson%2C%20Akbar%20(1542%E2%80%931605)%2C%20would%20become%20the%20greatest%20of%20the%20Mughal%20Emperors.%20He%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20great%20for%20waging%20wars%20or%20amassing%20territory%2C%20though%20he%20did%20that%20too%2C%20as%20emperors%20have%20long%20done%2C%20from%20Rome%20to%20Vijayanagar.%20Akbar%20was%20great%20because%20he%20was%20curious%2C%20fair-minded%2C%20and%20tolerant%2C%20and%20so%20he%20belongs%20with%20the%20greatest%20kings%20of%20India.%20It%20was%20Akbar%2C%20born%20in%20a%20Rajput%20fort%2C%20who%20turned%20the%20Mughals%20into%20an%20Indian%20dynasty.%20He%20was%20a%20practical%20man%3B%20instead%20of%20destroying%20his%20enemies%2C%20he%20tried%20to%20co-opt%20them%20into%20his%20imperial%20orbit.%20He%20built%20enduring%20alliances%20with%20many%20Rajput%20clans%2C%20cementing%20them%20through%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20household%20increasingly%20became%20multi-ethnic%20and%20multi-religious.%20Under%20his%20reign%2C%20freedom%20of%20religion%20was%20the%20norm.%20His%20Hindu%20wives%20passed%20down%20their%20cultural%20beliefs%20and%20values%20to%20their%20children%E2%80%94and%20to%20Akbar%2C%20who%20joined%20their%20festive%20celebrations%20of%20Holi%2C%20Janmashtami%2C%20and%20Diwali.%20His%20favourite%20wife%20was%20a%20Rajput%20woman%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20Jodha%20Bai.%20Known%20for%20her%20beauty%20and%20intellect%2C%20she%20is%20said%20to%20have%20nudged%20Akbar%20towards%20a%20more%20secular%20outlook.%20She%20was%20also%20the%20mother%20of%20the%20next%20Mughal%20emperor%2C%20Jahangir%20(1569%E2%80%931627).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Akbar%2C%20Hindus%20gained%20some%20of%20the%20choicest%20roles%20in%20the%20Mughal%20administration%2C%20military%2C%20and%20court.%20Think%20of%20Man%20Singh%2C%20Todar%20Mal%2C%20Tansen.%20Or%20his%20advisor%20Birbal%2C%20immortalised%20for%20his%20wit%20and%20intelligence%20in%20the%20supremely%20popular%20folk%20tales%20of%20Akbar%20and%20Birbal.%20At%20provincial%20levels%20too%2C%20his%20administration%20brought%20upward%20mobility%20to%20Hindu%20merchants%2C%20revenue%20collectors%2C%20Brahmins%2C%20and%20others%E2%80%94a%20trend%20that%20only%20increased%20in%20later%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkbar%20even%20abolished%20the%20jizya%20tax%20that%20dated%20from%20the%20Sultanate%20period.%20Jizya%20was%20exclusively%20levied%20on%20non-Muslims%20though%20the%20Rajputs%20and%20all%20Hindu%20employees%20of%20the%20State%20were%20exempt%20from%20it.%20Somehow%2C%20the%20Brahmins%20also%20got%20themselves%20exempted%20from%20it%20all%20along.%20Jizya%20was%20an%20unfair%20and%20resented%20tax%2C%20but%20it%20was%20poorly%20collected%20in%20practice%2C%20especially%20outside%20urban%20centres.%20The%20Brahmins%20didn%E2%80%99t%20pay%20jizya%20tax%20even%20under%20Aurangzeb%2C%20who%20reimposed%20it%20for%2040%20years%20against%20the%20wishes%20of%20his%20family%20and%20court.%20And%20thanks%20to%20the%20narrow%20solidarities%20of%20caste%2C%20the%20Brahmins%20never%20seem%20to%20have%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20protest%20its%20imposition%20on%20others%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkbar%20in%20fact%20presided%20over%20a%20great%20fusion%20of%20Rajput%20and%20Mughal%20cultures%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20the%20Sanskritic%20and%20Persianate%20worlds.%20It%E2%80%99s%20evident%20in%20the%20art%2C%20architecture%2C%20music%2C%20and%20cuisine%20of%20the%20Mughal%20era.%20Think%20of%20the%20arts%20of%20kathak%2C%20ghazal%2C%20khyal%20gayiki%2C%20and%20miniature%20painting.%20Consider%20the%20fusion%20of%20styles%20in%20the%20Govinda%20Deva%20Temple%20of%20Vrindavan%2C%20built%20with%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20enthusiastic%20support%2C%20or%20the%20sublime%20Indo-Persian%20architecture%20of%20his%20short-lived%20capital%2C%20Fatehpur%20Sikri.%20Akbar%20had%20suffered%20from%20dyslexia%2C%20and%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20read%20or%20write.%20But%20he%20had%20a%20sharp%20memory%20and%20maintained%20a%20huge%20library%20of%2024%2C000%20books%2C%20staffed%20by%20scholars%2C%20translators%2C%20calligraphers%2C%20scribes%2C%20as%20well%20as%20readers%20who%20read%20books%20to%20him%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkbar%20is%20also%20known%20for%20his%20moving%20spiritual%20quest.%20Though%20raised%20a%20Sunni%20Muslim%2C%20he%20felt%20that%20religious%20truth%20transcended%20any%20one%20religion%2C%20that%20it%20is%20scattered%20across%20religions.%20To%20discover%20it%20for%20himself%2C%20Akbar%20sponsored%20inter-faith%20debates%20for%20which%20he%20invited%20theologians%2C%20poets%2C%20scholars%2C%20and%20philosophers%20from%20many%20religious%20traditions%2C%20including%20Muslims%2C%20Christians%2C%20Hindus%2C%20Jains%2C%20and%20Zoroastrians.%20He%20explored%20various%20ideas.%20He%20patronised%20Chishti%20saints.%20He%20banned%20cow%20slaughter.%20At%20one%20time%2C%20he%20even%20turned%20vegetarian%2C%20adopted%20the%20hairstyle%20of%20ascetics%2C%20began%20venerating%20the%20sun%20and%20learned%20the%201001%20Sanskrit%20names%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkbar%20eventually%20created%20a%20new%20syncretic%20religion%20in%201582.%20He%20called%20it%20Din-i%20Ilahi%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98divine%20religion%E2%80%99.%20This%20angered%20many%20orthodox%20clerics%20of%20Islam%E2%80%94a%20good%20indication%20that%20he%20was%20trying%20something%20good.%20His%20new%20religion%20was%20drawn%20from%20multiple%20traditions%2C%20and%20included%20ideas%20like%20the%20love%20of%20God%2C%20ahimsa%2C%20and%20even%20a%20fire%20ritual.%20But%20not%20many%20of%20his%20subjects%20were%20persuaded%2C%20and%20Din-i%20Ilahi%20faded%20after%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20death%20in%201605.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBernier%20in%20Shahjahanabad%2C%20Delhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20Mughal%20Emperor%2C%20Jahangir%20continued%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20fascination%20with%20older%20Indian%20religions.%20He%20too%20sponsored%20inter-faith%20debates%2C%20and%20often%20visited%20a%20Hindu%20ascetic%20called%20Jadrup%2C%20near%20Ujjain.%20Jahangir%20not%20only%20favoured%20freedom%20of%20religion%2C%20he%20strictly%20opposed%20non-voluntary%20conversions.%20Like%20his%20father%2C%20Jahangir%20too%20married%20an%20intelligent%20and%20beautiful%20Rajput%20princess%2C%20Jagat%20Gosain.%20Their%20marriage%20involved%20dual%20ceremonies%2C%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20How%20modern%20was%20that!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20Jahan%20(1592%E2%80%93%201666)%2C%20the%20next%20emperor%2C%20was%20born%20from%20this%20union%2C%20which%20made%20him%2075%20percent%20Rajput%20by%20ancestry.%20Shah%20Jahan%20would%20build%20some%20of%20the%20most%20spectacular%20monuments%20of%20Mughal%20India%2C%20like%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%2C%20Shalimar%20Gardens%2C%20the%20Red%20Fort%20and%20Jama%20Masjid.%20In%201648%2C%20he%20moved%20his%20capital%20from%20Agra%20to%20Shahjahanabad.%20The%20British%20maliciously%20destroyed%20large%20parts%20of%20it%20after%201857.%20What%20remains%20is%20now%20in%20Old%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201658%2C%20the%20last%20year%20of%20Shah%20Jahan%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20a%20French%20doctor%2C%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Bernier%2C%20came%20to%20Delhi%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20physician%20to%20Dara%20Shikoh%2C%20the%20eldest%20son%20of%20Shah%20Jahan.%20But%20within%20months%20of%20his%20arrival%20came%20the%20bloody%20war%20of%20royal%20succession%2C%20in%20which%20Aurangzeb%20eliminated%20his%20three%20brothers%20and%20imprisoned%20his%20father%2C%20Shah%20Jahan.%20Bernier%20described%20this%20battle%20in%20fair%20detail.%20He%20thought%20Dara%20Shikoh%20was%20%E2%80%98extremely%20liberal%E2%80%99%20and%20erudite%2C%20not%20the%20least%20for%20translating%20the%20Upanishads%20into%20Persian.%20Dara%20hated%20Aurangzeb%2C%20and%20called%20him%20a%20%E2%80%98Nemazi%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98Bigot%E2%80%99.%20But%20it%20was%20Aurangzeb%20who%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20witnessed%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20He%20worked%20for%20a%20nobleman%2C%20Daneshmand%20Khan%2C%20who%20had%20moved%20to%20Delhi%20from%20Persia%2C%20and%20was%20the%20Mughal%20secretary%20of%20state%20for%20foreign%20affairs%20and%20grand%20master%20of%20the%20horse.%20In%20Bernier%E2%80%99s%20letters%20to%20people%20back%20home%2C%20later%20published%20as%20Travels%20in%20the%20Mogul%20Empire%2C%20he%20warmly%20referred%20to%20Khan%20as%20%E2%80%98my%20Agah%E2%80%99%20%5Bchief%2C%20master%5D%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20most%20learned%20man%20of%20Asia%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98whose%20thirst%20for%20knowledge%20is%20incessant%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20who%20voraciously%20read%20works%20on%20astronomy%2C%20geography%2C%20anatomy%2C%20the%20materialist%20philosophy%20of%20Gassendi%2C%20Descartes%2C%20and%20more.%20Khan%20and%20a%20few%20kindred%20%E2%80%98Moguls%E2%80%99%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20intellectuals%20in%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20with%20no%20evident%20counterparts%20in%20Hindu%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%2C%20according%20to%20Bernier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20public%20architecture%20of%20Mughal%20Delhi%20and%20Agra.%20In%20terms%20of%20beauty%2C%20he%20considered%20it%20on%20par%20with%20the%20best%20in%20France%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Palais%20Royale.%20Delhi%20had%20wide%20streets%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20on%20which%20Muslim%20and%20Hindu%20noblemen%20ride%2C%20%E2%80%98some%20on%20horseback%2C%20some%20on%20majestic%20elephants%3B%20but%20the%20greater%20part%20are%20conveyed%20on%20the%20shoulders%20of%20men%2C%20in%20rich%20Palekys%2C%20leaning%20against%20a%20thick%20cushion%20of%20brocade%2C%20and%20chewing%20their%20%5Bpaan%5D%2C%20for%20the%20double%20purpose%20of%20sweetening%20their%20breath%20and%20reddening%20their%20lips.%E2%80%99%20Chances%20are%20that%20such%20visuals%20have%20a%20long%20history%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20described%20the%20opulence%20of%20the%20emperor%20and%20his%20courtiers%2C%20their%20grand%20processions%2C%20lavish%20costumes%2C%20the%20audience%20hall%20at%20Red%20Fort%20with%20its%20peacock%20throne%20and%20rich%20furnishings%20of%20silver%2C%20gold%20brocade%2C%20silk%20and%20satin.%20He%20observed%20%E2%80%98the%20base%20and%20disgusting%20adulation%20which%20is%20invariably%20witnessed%20there%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98the%20vice%20of%20flattery%20%5Bthat%5D%20pervades%20all%20ranks%E2%80%99.%20But%20the%20common%20man%E2%80%99s%20life%20was%20very%20different.%20%E2%80%98In%20Dehli%20there%20is%20no%20middle%20state%E2%80%99%2C%20wrote%20Bernier.%20%E2%80%98A%20man%20must%20either%20be%20of%20the%20highest%20rank%20or%20live%20miserably.%E2%80%99%20He%20contrasted%20this%20with%20Paris%2C%20where%20poverty%20and%20disparity%20were%20not%20so%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20saw%20India%20as%20a%20vast%20collection%20of%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20groups%2C%20with%20no%20common%20%E2%80%98Indian%E2%80%99%20identity.%20Which%20makes%20sense%E2%80%94an%20%E2%80%98Indian%E2%80%99%20identity%20only%20emerged%20during%20the%20colonial%20struggle%20in%20the%2019th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bernier%E2%80%99s%20day%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98Mughal%E2%80%99%20mainly%20referred%20to%20light-skinned%20Persianate%20Muslims%20with%20recent%20ancestry%20outside%20the%20subcontinent.%20Mughals%20had%20higher%20social%20status.%20According%20to%20Bernier%2C%20they%20sought%20out%20light-skinned%20Kashmiri%20women%20for%20marriage.%20Such%20Muslims%20dominated%20the%20best%20imperial%20positions%2C%20alongside%20a%20few%20Rajputs%20and%20other%20Hindus.%20Skin%20colour%20had%20long%20obsessed%20Hindus%20too%2C%20so%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20new%20concept.%20Our%20modern%20preference%20for%20%E2%80%98gore-chitte%E2%80%99%20%5Blight-skinned%5D%20women%20goes%20way%20back%20to%20the%20Indo-Aryans.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20Indo-Muslim%20rule%20was%20replacing%20an%20earlier%20lighter-skinned%20elite%20with%20a%20newer%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20described%20the%20luxurious%20but%20cloistered%20lives%20of%20women%20in%20the%20Mughal%20harem.%20Only%20royal%20men%20could%20visit%20them%2C%20so%20his%20account%20was%20based%20on%20what%20he%20had%20heard.%20Their%20%E2%80%98consumption%20of%20fine%20cloths%20of%20gold%2C%20and%20brocades%2C%20silks%2C%20embroideries%2C%20pearls%2C%20musk%2C%20amber%20and%20sweet%20essences%2C%20is%20greater%20than%20can%20be%20imagined%E2%80%99%2C%20wrote%20Bernier.%20Shah%20Jahan%20had%20invited%20singing%20and%20dancing%20girls%20in%20the%20harem%2C%20%E2%80%98and%20amused%20himself%20with%20their%20antics%20and%20follies%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20Aurangzeb%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20that.%20According%20to%20Bernier%2C%20Aurangzeb%20was%20%E2%80%98more%20serious%20than%20his%20father%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98anxious%20to%20appear%20a%20true%20Musulman%E2%80%99.%20Children%20too%20lived%20in%20the%20harem.%20Its%20walled%20compound%20had%20its%20own%20bazaars%2C%20kitchens%2C%20schools%20and%20playgrounds.%20The%20women%20of%20the%20harem%20were%20guarded%20by%20eunuchs.%20They%20could%20only%20go%20out%20in%20purdah%2C%20carried%20in%20palkees.%20It%E2%80%99s%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20between%20the%20Turko-Persian%20and%20Brahminical%20patriarchies%2C%20the%20goose%20of%20Indian%20women%20was%20pretty%20well%20cooked!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBernier%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20realities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20noted%20that%20some%20parts%20of%20India%20were%20relatively%20affluent.%20Fertile%20Bengal%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20produced%20ample%20rice%2C%20corn%2C%20silks%2C%20cotton%2C%20and%20indigo.%20Its%20handloom%20workers%20manufactured%20silk%20and%20cotton%20textiles%2C%20carpets%2C%20embroideries%20and%20brocades%2C%20often%20for%20export%20overseas.%20But%20most%20regions%20were%20not%20so%20lucky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20land%20belonged%20to%20the%20crown%2C%20wrote%20Bernier.%20People%20could%20not%20legally%20own%2C%20buy%20or%20sell%20land%2C%20though%20they%20could%20use%20it%20as%20long%20as%20they%20paid%20their%20preset%20revenue%20to%20the%20king.%20This%20had%20been%20the%20case%20at%20least%20since%20Mauryan%20times.%20Bernier%20compared%20this%20with%20the%20private%20property%20regime%20that%20many%20European%20states%20had%20recently%20evolved.%20He%20considers%20this%20a%20major%20reason%20why%20Europeans%20had%20grown%20richer.%20Because%20Indians%20could%20lose%20their%20land%20to%20the%20whims%20of%20power%2C%20they%20had%20less%20incentive%20to%20invest%20in%20it.%20This%20not%20only%20reduced%20their%20income%2C%20Bernier%20argued%2C%20it%20also%20depressed%20tax%20revenues%20for%20the%20king%2C%20and%20encouraged%20people%20to%20hide%20their%20surpluses%20in%20gold.%20Formal%20property%20rights%20in%20India%20would%20arise%20only%20in%20the%20British%20colonial%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20made%20things%20even%20worse%2C%20wrote%20Bernier%2C%20is%20that%20provincial%20governors%20and%20tax%20collectors%20exercised%20their%20authority%20over%20the%20peasantry%20in%20oppressive%20ways.%20This%20feudal%20system%20of%20non-hereditary%20land%20tenure%20was%20pan-Indian%2C%20and%20it%20dated%20from%20the%20Gupta%20period.%20Bernier%20blamed%20this%20%E2%80%98miserable%20system%20of%20government%E2%80%99%2C%20combining%20despotic%20power%20with%20lack%20of%20private%20property%2C%20for%20why%20Indians%20were%20worse%20off%20than%20Europeans%2C%20and%20why%20%E2%80%98most%20towns%20in%20Hindoustan%20are%20made%20up%20of%20earth%2C%20mud%2C%20and%20other%20wretched%20materials%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20scholars%20find%20Bernier%E2%80%99s%20account%20too%20bleak%20and%20oversimplified%2C%20but%20it%20does%20reveal%20a%20powerful%2C%20extractive%20bureaucracy%20concentrating%20riches%20at%20the%20top%2C%20sustaining%20a%20huge%20army%2C%20and%20funding%20the%20lavish%20lives%20of%20the%20aristocrats.%20As%20we%20saw%20in%20the%20previous%20episode%2C%20this%20was%20also%20true%20in%20Vijayanagar.%20Bernier%E2%80%99s%20portrait%20of%20the%20extreme%20disparities%20in%20India%20agrees%20with%20other%20testimonies%2C%20like%20that%20of%20the%20pre-Mughal%20Russian%20traveller%2C%20Afanasy%20Nikitin%3A%20%E2%80%98Those%20in%20the%20countryside%20are%20very%20miserable%2C%20whilst%20the%20nobles%20are%20extremely%20opulent%20and%20delight%20in%20luxury.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20testimonies%20refute%20the%20sone%20ki%20chidiya%20(%E2%80%98golden%20bird%E2%80%99)%20metaphor%20about%20pre-colonial%20India%2C%20which%20suggests%20that%20India%20was%20a%20disproportionately%20rich%20country%20in%20medieval%20times.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20true.%20Some%20popular%20historians%20say%2C%20correctly%2C%20that%20in%201700%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20global%20GDP%20was%20around%2024%20percent.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20also%20say%20that%20its%20share%20of%20the%20world%20population%20was%20around%2027%20percent.%20Which%20placed%20India%E2%80%99s%20per%20capita%20income%20below%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20that%20too%20many%20of%20the%20inflated%20claims%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20pre-colonial%20riches%20are%20based%20on%20foreign%20travellers%E2%80%99%20accounts%20of%20wealthy%20elites%E2%80%94even%20as%20the%20commoners%20were%20no%20better%20off%20than%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20And%20how%20could%20they%20be%3F%20For%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20most%20people%20in%20the%20world%20had%20lived%20off%20labour%20intensive%20farming%2C%20pastoralism%2C%20hunting%2C%20gathering%2C%20or%20small%20trades%2C%20producing%20similar%20standards%20of%20living.%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20per%20capita%20incomes%20did%20not%20change%20much%20until%20the%20mid-20th%20century%2C%20but%20European%20incomes%20surged%20earlier%2C%20driven%20by%20their%20colonial%20projects%20and%20their%20scientific%20and%20industrial%20revolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBernier%20on%20Hindu%20customs%20and%20superstitions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20was%20a%20man%20of%20the%20early%20Enlightenment%20and%20a%20big%20believer%20in%20science%20and%20reason.%20He%20saw%20himself%20as%20part%20of%20a%20more%20%E2%80%98advanced%E2%80%99%20civilization%2C%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20scientific%20knowledge%20and%20its%20social%20and%20political%20thought.%20What%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20seen%20is%20that%20his%20civilization%20had%20embarked%20on%20a%20path%20that%20would%20lead%20all%20humanity%20to%20the%20edge%20of%20our%20catastrophic%20climate%20change%20and%20sixth%20mass%20extinction.%20But%20that%20story%2C%20another%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20Bernier%20was%20not%20impressed%20by%20the%20state%20of%20Indian%20science%20or%20medicine.%20The%20Hindus%20%E2%80%98understand%20nothing%20of%20anatomy%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20wrote%2C%20because%20%E2%80%98they%20never%20open%20the%20body%20either%20of%20man%20or%20beast%E2%80%99.%20To%20explain%20the%20details%20of%20blood%20circulation%20that%20William%20Harvey%20had%20recently%20discovered%2C%20Bernier%20cut%20open%20living%20goats%20and%20sheep%20before%20his%20horrified%20hosts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20bothered%20him%20the%20most%20were%20superstitions%20that%20caused%20injury%20and%20death.%20He%20was%20revolted%20by%20the%20Rath%20Yatra%20(car)%20festival%20at%20the%20Jagannath%20Temple%20in%20Puri%2C%20where%20some%20%E2%80%98fanatics%E2%80%99%20died%20by%20throwing%20themselves%20under%20the%20wheels%20of%20a%20giant%20wooden%20chariot.%20Bernier%20saw%20Brahmins%20as%20promoting%20such%20customs%20to%20ensure%20their%20own%20livelihood.%20He%20criticised%20%E2%80%98lustful%20priests%E2%80%99%20who%20deceived%20and%20possessed%20young%20girls%20dedicated%20to%20serve%20the%20gods%20of%20Jagannath%20Temple.%20He%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Great%20Mogol%20%5BAurangzeb%5D%20%E2%80%A6%20permits%20these%20ancient%20and%20superstitious%20practices%3B%20not%20wishing%2C%20or%20not%20daring%2C%20to%20disturb%20the%20Gentiles%20%5BHindus%5D%20in%20the%20free%20exercises%20of%20their%20religion.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20custom%20that%20bothered%20Bernier%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98melancholy%20fact%E2%80%99%20of%20sati%2C%20mostly%20practised%20among%20the%20upper-caste%20warrior%20elite.%20He%20was%20certain%20that%20fewer%20widows%20would%20follow%20it%2C%20if%20given%20the%20choice%20%E2%80%98by%20the%20merciless%20Brahmens%E2%80%99%20but%20instead%2C%20the%20women%20were%20often%20physically%20forced%20into%20it.%20Bernier%20observed%20that%20any%20widow%20who%20managed%20to%20%E2%80%98avoid%20the%20impending%20sacrifice%2C%20cannot%20hope%20to%20pass%20her%20days%20in%20happiness%2C%20or%20to%20be%20treated%20with%20respect%20or%20affection%20.%20.%20.%20she%20is%20ever%20afterwards%20exposed%20to%20the%20ill-treatment%20of%20her%20low%20and%20vulgar%20protectors%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mughals%20under%20Aurangzeb%2C%20wrote%20Bernier%2C%20do%20not%20interfere%20with%20%E2%80%98the%20idolatrous%20population%20%E2%80%A6%20in%20the%20free%20exercise%20of%20its%20religion%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20they%20try%20to%20discourage%20sati%20by%20other%20means%2C%20as%20in%20requiring%20permission%20for%20it%20from%20the%20local%20governor.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20they%20try%20to%20dissuade%20the%20widow%20and%20others%20involved.%20This%20often%20works%2C%20but%20not%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20territories%20of%20the%20%5BRajput%5D%20Rajas%2C%20where%20no%20%5BMuslim%5D%20governors%20are%20appointed.%E2%80%99%20The%20fact%20is%20that%20sati%20was%20more%20common%20in%20autonomous%20Hindu%20kingdoms%2C%20such%20as%20of%20the%20Rajputs%20and%20earlier%20of%20Vijayanagar%2C%20and%20it%20declined%20in%20areas%20that%20came%20under%20direct%20Mughal%20rule.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20true%20that%20in%20non-elite%20groups%2C%20sati%20was%20largely%20absent%2C%20where%20widows%20could%20even%20remarry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20had%20his%20limitations.%20He%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20read%20any%20Indian%20languages.%20He%20had%20his%20blindspots%20of%20comprehension%20and%20creed.%20But%20he%20also%20had%20a%20humanistic%20ethos%20and%20was%20often%20very%20clear-eyed.%20In%20his%20insightful%20account%2C%20Indians%20seem%20to%20be%20mired%20in%20feudal%20and%20social%20inequities%2C%20ignorance%20and%20superstition%E2%80%94and%2C%20in%20hindsight%2C%20utterly%20ill-prepared%20against%20the%20advancing%20might%20of%20European%20science%20and%20technology%2C%20mercantilism%2C%20scholarship%2C%20and%20militarised%20nation-states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20myths%20about%20the%20Mughals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20all%20empires%2C%20the%20Mughals%2C%20too%2C%20have%20a%20mixed%20record%20and%20deserve%20criticism%20on%20many%20fronts.%20They%20too%20represented%20an%20extractive%20and%20exploitative%20imperial%20order.%20While%20they%20did%20build%20roads%2C%20provide%20a%20unified%20market%2C%20and%20a%20stable%2C%20common%20currency%2C%20they%20also%20fought%20too%20many%20wars%20of%20expansion%2C%20often%20in%20pursuit%20of%20personal%20glory%20and%20vanity.%20They%20spent%20on%20high%20culture%20and%20big%20monuments%2C%20but%20not%20so%20much%20on%20public%20welfare%20or%20education.%20They%20greatly%20expanded%20cultivation%20to%20increase%20land%20revenue%2C%20but%20it%20often%20came%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20most%20long-lasting%2C%20multi-ethnic%2C%20and%20multilingual%20empires%2C%20the%20Mughal%20rulers%20were%20also%20pragmatic%2C%20not%20narrowly%20ideological%E2%80%94except%20for%20Aurangzeb.%20His%20follies%20caused%20sectarian%20strife%20and%20peasant%20revolts%2C%20which%20contributed%20to%20the%20decline%20of%20the%20Mughal%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20(arguably)%20fair%20criticisms%2C%20but%20the%20Mughals%20have%20also%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20unfair%20cultural%20criticism%2C%20especially%20from%20Hindu%20nationalists.%20They%20allege%20that%20most%20Mughals%20forcibly%20converted%20Hindus%20to%20Islam%20on%20a%20large%20scale%2C%20and%20indiscriminately%20desecrated%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20temples.%20These%20allegations%20have%20been%20turbocharged%20in%20our%20age%20of%20social%20media%20and%20WhatsApp%20university.%20Are%20they%20true%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20forced%20conversions%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernier%20did%20not%20mention%20any%20religious%20persecution%20of%20%E2%80%98the%20Gentiles%E2%80%99%2C%20nor%20forced%20conversions%2C%20likely%20because%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20see%20any.%20To%20the%20extent%20they%20happened%2C%20they%20remained%20exceedingly%20rare.%20The%20thing%20is%20that%20forced%20conversions%20rarely%20succeed%3B%20people%20just%20revert%20to%20their%20old%20faiths%20when%20the%20tyrant%20is%20gone.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20conversions%20(in%20India)%20happened%20voluntarily.%20Most%20converts%20were%20lower-caste%20Hindus%20drawn%20to%20something%20in%20Islam%2C%20which%20likely%20included%20its%20promise%20of%20spiritual%20equality%20among%20all%20believers.%20Perhaps%20they%20also%20saw%20many%20mundane%20benefits%20of%20embracing%20the%20rulers%E2%80%99%20faith%20and%20culture%2C%20such%20as%20better%20education%2C%20social%20mobility%2C%20and%20job%20prospects.%20Sufi%20shaikhs%20played%20a%20role%20too.%20The%20Chishti%20saint%2C%20Khwaja%20Moinuddin%2C%20was%20popularly%20called%20%E2%80%98Gharib%20Nawaz%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20comforter%20of%20the%20poor.%20The%20Chishti%20order%20fed%20people%20in%20an%20open%20kitchen%2C%20or%20langar%2C%20a%20practice%20that%20was%20institutionalised%20in%20Sikhism%20but%20never%20cut%20any%20ice%20with%20the%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20believe%20that%20the%20pressure%20to%20convert%20was%20high%2C%20think%20of%20all%20the%20caste%20Hindu%20allies%20of%20the%20Mughals%2C%20who%20were%20Rajputs%2C%20Marathas%2C%20Kayasthas%2C%20Brahmins.%20They%20did%20not%20convert%2C%20even%20though%20they%20were%20the%20closest%20to%20the%20Mughals.%20Interfaith%20marriages%20required%20no%20conversion%2C%20even%20by%20the%20emperors%20themselves.%20So%2C%20what%20pressure%20are%20we%20talking%20about%3F%20In%20the%20early%2018th%20century%2C%20after%20500%20years%20of%20Indo-Muslim%20rule%2C%20converts%20formed%20hardly%2010%E2%80%9312%25%20of%20the%20subcontinental%20population.%20They%20were%20even%20fewer%20in%20the%20Mughal%20heartland%20in%20north-central%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20remember%20that%20the%20Indo-Muslim%20period%20saw%20a%20great%20flowering%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Bhakti%20tradition%20in%20north%20India%2C%20through%20figures%20like%20Chaitanya%2C%20Tukaram%2C%20Kabir%2C%20Ravidas%2C%20Nanak%2C%20Mirabai%2C%20Eknath%2C%20Tulsidas%20and%20many%20others.%20The%20Ram%20Katha%20and%20Ram%20Lila%20traditions%20emerged%20and%20flourished%20in%20this%20period.%20I%20think%20all%20of%20this%20refutes%20the%20theory%20that%20the%20Mughals%20persecuted%20and%20forcibly%20converted%20large%20numbers%20of%20Hindus.%20Or%2C%20as%20a%20judge%20might%20say%3A%20case%20dismissed!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20temple%20desecrations%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20temple%20desecrations%20or%20destructions%2C%20they%20did%20happen.%20In%20the%20centuries%20before%20Indo-Muslim%20rule%2C%20Hindu%20kings%20had%20done%20it%20too%2C%20though%20its%20frequency%20increased%20under%20Indo-Muslims.%20But%20this%20frequency%20was%20far%20below%20the%20absurd%20numbers%20claimed%20by%20Hindu%20nationalists.%20They%E2%80%99re%20based%20on%20cherry-picked%20details%2C%20especially%20from%20Indo-Muslim%20court%20chronicles%2C%20which%2C%20as%20you%E2%80%99d%20expect%2C%20greatly%20inflate%20their%20patron%E2%80%99s%20military%2C%20sexual%2C%20and%20religious%20exploits.%20Academic%20historians%20have%20investigated%20deeper%20for%20more%20rigorous%20evidence.%20According%20to%20historian%20Richard%20Eaton%2C%20the%20verifiable%20cases%20of%20temple%20desecrations%20are%20less%20than%20a%20hundred%2C%20over%20more%20than%20five%20centuries.%20The%20Mughals%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20treated%20temples%20in%20their%20domain%20as%20state%20property%20and%20protected%20%E2%80%98both%20the%20physical%20structures%20and%20their%20Brahmin%20functionaries%E2%80%99.%20The%20Brahmins%20continued%20to%20live%20tax%20free%2C%20as%20they%20had%20done%20since%20Ashoka.%20Aurangzeb%20himself%20funded%20many%20temples%20with%20land%20and%20money%2C%20even%20as%20he%20destroyed%20some%20others.%20How%20can%20we%20explain%20this%20apparent%20contradiction%3F%20Scholars%20have%20looked%20at%20the%20evidence%20and%20identified%20important%20patterns%20behind%20temple%20desecrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20worth%20remembering%20that%20Hindu%20kings%20derived%20their%20divine%20right%20to%20rule%20from%20specific%20lineages%E2%80%94like%20chandravanshis%20and%20suryavanshis%20among%20the%20Rajputs.%20And%20they%20patronised%20state%20temples%20dedicated%20to%20specific%20deities.%20These%20were%20the%20types%20of%20temples%20that%20Indo-Muslim%20rulers%20usually%20targeted.%20They%20were%20politically%20salient%20for%20their%20association%20with%20rival%20Hindu%20kings.%20Desecrating%20them%20damaged%20their%20rival%E2%80%99s%20prestige%20and%20legitimacy%20to%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it%20would%20be%20foolish%20to%20argue%20that%20every%20single%20temple%20desecration%20under%20the%20Mughals%20had%20purely%20political%20motives.%20No%2C%20sometimes%2C%20religious%20motives%20mattered%20too%2C%20especially%20with%20Aurangzeb%2C%20a%20puritanical%20man.%20But%20the%20primary%20motivation%20for%20temple%20desecrations%20was%20political%2C%20not%20religious.%20Besides%2C%20how%20long%20could%20a%20ruler%20act%20out%20of%20openly%20sectarian%20motives%3F%20Remember%20that%20the%20Mughals%20had%20lots%20of%20Rajput%20and%20Maratha%20allies%2C%20Hindu%20administrators%20and%20soldiers%2C%20whose%20numbers%20had%20steadily%20increased%20and%20become%20the%20highest%20under%20Aurangzeb.%20This%20had%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20any%20religious%20adventurism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20additional%20complexities.%20In%20medieval%20times%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20Hindus%E2%80%99%20were%20deeply%20fragmented.%20Hinduism%20simply%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20organised%20enough%20to%20be%20targeted%20as%20a%20whole.%20People%20identified%20not%20with%20a%20common%20religion%20but%20with%20particular%20sects%2C%20gods%2C%20and%20rituals.%20They%20may%20not%20have%20seen%20a%20royal%20temple%E2%80%99s%20desecration%20as%20an%20attack%20on%20their%20own%20faith.%20Many%20of%20the%20subjects%20were%20likely%20not%20even%20allowed%20to%20enter%20a%20royal%20temple%3B%20would%20they%20have%20been%20hurt%20by%20its%20desecration%3F%20Often%2C%20desecrations%20would%20have%20hurt%20just%20an%20urban%20microcosm%20close%20to%20the%20rival%20king.%20In%20short%2C%20temple%20desecrations%20were%20less%20about%20%E2%80%98attacking%20Hinduism%E2%80%99%2C%20more%20about%20political%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20only%20hope%20that%20such%20arguments%20at%20least%20become%20kabab%20mein%20haddi%E2%80%94or%20bones%20in%20the%20ideological%20kabab%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20hegemonic%20narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20all%20that%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20true%20that%20Brahminical%20Hinduism%20received%20less%20patronage%20under%20the%20Deccan%20Sultanates%20and%20the%20Mughals%2C%20compared%20to%2C%20say%2C%20in%20Vijayanagar.%20Under%20the%20Indo-Muslims%2C%20Hindus%20had%20to%20share%20the%20royal%20patronage%20once%20again%2C%20as%20they%20did%20under%20Ashoka%20and%20Harsha.%20A%20similar%20reduction%20in%20leadership%20roles%20also%20occurred%20for%20Hindus%20under%20most%20Indo-Muslim%20regimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%E2%80%99s%20also%20true%20is%20that%20this%20mainly%20impacted%20one%20section%20of%20the%20urban%20upper-caste%20Hindus.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20recognize%20that%20the%20losses%20suffered%20by%20this%20small%20minority%20cannot%20be%20conflated%20with%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20vast%20majority%E2%80%94including%20shudras%2C%20outcastes%2C%20and%20tribal%20groups.%20Most%20other%20people%20either%20happily%20continued%20with%20their%20own%20religious%20traditions%2C%20converted%20to%20Islam%2C%20or%20adopted%20syncretic%20religious%20forms%2C%20like%20the%20ultra%20popular%20devotional%20movements%20of%20Bhakti%20and%20Sufism%2C%20which%20relied%20on%20vernacular%20tongues%2C%20and%20captivating%20dance%20and%20musical%20expressions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20always%2C%20in%20the%20grand%20march%20of%20history%2C%20continuity%2C%20disruption%2C%20and%20renewal%20were%20all%20in%20play.%20History%20is%20not%20as%20black-and-white%20as%20Hindu%20nationalists%20today%E2%80%94led%20by%20upper-caste%20Hindus!%E2%80%94so%20often%20think%20it%20is.%20The%20narrative%20manufactured%20by%20this%20hegemonic%2C%20yet%20culturally-insecure%20minority%20is%20neither%20truthful%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20represent%20the%20diverse%20experiences%20of%20Hindus%20and%20other%20groups%20under%20the%20Mughals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20to%20digest!%20I%E2%80%99ll%20say%20more%20about%20our%20love-hate%20relationship%20with%20the%20Mughals%20in%20the%20next%20episode%2C%20with%20specific%20examples%20from%20the%20history%20of%20Varanasi%2C%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20living%20cities%20in%20the%20world.%20From%20its%20antiquity%20as%20Kashi%20to%20its%20life%20under%20the%20Mughals%20and%20beyond%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20explore%20why%20Varanasi%20lies%20so%20much%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20our%20Indian%20civilization.%20See%20you%20next%20time!%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709721045000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F06151641%2Fimage-1908.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-episode-9-the-mughals-and-bernier%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20episode%20explores%20French%20doctor%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Bernier's%20insightful%20accounts%20on%20the%20Mughal%20courtly%20culture%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20economic%20condition%20of%20Indians%2C%20their%20science%20and%20intellectual%20life%2C%20and%20Hindu%20cultural%20and%20religious%20customs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-episode-9-the-mughals-and-bernier%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aryan%20's%20latest%