%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2003884%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMinistry%2520of%2520Home%2520Affairs%2520(MHA%2CNorth%2520Eastern%2520States%2520bordering%2520Myanmar%5C%22%3Ethat%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20to%20end%20the%20bilateral%20understanding%20with%20the%20neighbouring%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20MEA%20has%20thus%20far%20not%20issued%20any%20formal%20statement%20on%20the%20MHA%E2%80%99s%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%204%2C%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20Winter%20Session%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%2C%20Biren%20Singh%20said%20the%20FMR%20has%20not%20been%20scrapped%20yet.%20%E2%80%9CNonetheless%2C%20the%20state%20government%20has%20been%20suspending%20the%20FMR%20for%20every%20six%20months%20with%20due%20consent%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesangaiexpress.com%2FEncyc%2F2024%2F3%2F6%2FBy-Our-Staff-ReporterIMPHAL-Mar-5-Even-though-the-Ministry-of-Home-Affairs-has-written-to-the-Ministry-of.html%5C%22%3Ehe%20said.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20reply%20to%20a%20question%20by%20MLA%20and%20state%20Congress%20chief%20Meghachandra%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Manipur%20state%20administration%20had%20suspended%20the%20FMR%20with%20Myanmar%20since%202021%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20arrangement%20has%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20latest%20notification%20for%20suspension%20of%20FMR%20was%20issued%20on%20February%2016%20this%20year.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20issue%20an%20order%20whereby%20FMR%20would%20be%20scrapped%20totally%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20chief%20minister%20told%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20referring%20to%20some%20recent%20media%20reports%20about%20the%20arres