0former%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%2C%20constituted%20to%20look%20into%20the%20question%20of%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20is%20learnt%20to%20have%20approved%20most%20of%20the%20suggestions%20by%20the%20Law%20Commission.%20The%20Kovind%20committee%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20simultaneous%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20sources%20cited%20by%20%3Cem%3ETNIE%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Law%20Commission%20may%20suggest%20introducing%20an%20additional%20chapter%20(Part%20XV-A)%2C%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment.%20Currently%2C%20Part%20XV%20of%20the%20constitution%20deals%20with%20elections.%20The%20new%20chapter%20will%20deal%20with%20issues%20related%20to%20%E2%80%9Csynchronised%20elections%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Csustainability%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccommon%20electoral%20roll%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20three-tier%20simultaneous%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20may%20also%20recommend%20forming%20a%20%E2%80%98unity%20government%E2%80%99%20in%20case%20a%20government%20falls%20due%20to%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%20or%20if%20there%20is%20a%20hung%20House.%20The%20resulting%20government%20may%20be%20formed%20with%20representatives%20from%20various%20political%20parties.%20Even%20if%20the%20unity%20government%20formula%20fails%2C%20the%20commission%20may%20suggest%20holding%20fresh%20elections%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20term%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%2021st%20Law%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20suggestions%2C%20which%20had%20favoured%20simultaneous%20polls%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20would%20save%20public%20money.%20However%2C%20it%20had%20said%20the%20same%20is%20not%20possible%20with%20the%20existing%20constitutional%20framework.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%20said%C2%A0the%20proposal%20can%20only%20be%20materialised%20by%20the%202029%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20as%20it%20would%2C%20over%20time%2C%20work