ces%20the%20need%20for%20raw%20material%20extraction%20for%20battery%20production.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20they%20used%2015%20different%20varieties%20of%20waste%20%E2%80%94%20including%20coconut%20shells%2C%20coconut%20husks%2C%20fruit%20stones%2C%20paper%20waste%2C%20palm%20kernel%20shells%2C%20and%20human%20hair%20waste%20%E2%80%94%20to%20upcycle%20them%20into%20useful%20nanocarbons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20from%20a%20business%20perspective%2C%20we%20found%20coconut%20shells%20as%20the%20right%20precursor%20because%20of%20their%20commercial%20feasibility%20and%20their%20wide%20availability%20and%20abundance.%20These%20precursors%20possess%20certain%20properties%20like%20high%20carbon%20content%2C%20hardness%20levels%2C%20and%20ash%20content%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20a%20better%20choice%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Akshay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20thermal%20treatment%20of%20agricultural%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20extracts%20black-coloured%20powder%2C%20known%20as%20nanocarbon.%20Compared%20to%20existing%20incumbent%20solutions%20used%20in%20batteries%2C%20it%20is%20claimed%20to%20have%20a%20better%20surface%20area%2C%20pore%20network%2C%20surface%20wettability%2C%20and%20functionalities%20%E2%80%94%20this%20enhances%20the%20electrochemical%20reactions%20on%20electrode%20plates%20at%20a%20molecular%20level%20in%20batteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEnhancing%20battery%20efficiency%20and%20lifespan%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20safely%20conducting%20the%20BIS%20standard%20testing%20for%20batteries%20using%20their%20nanocarbon%20at%20an%20industrial%20scale%2C%20the%20startup%20commercialised%20their%20product%20to%20leading%20battery%20manufacturers%20in%20the%20country.%20Mahi%20informs%20that%20at%20least%203%2C500%20batteries%20with%20Cancrie%20nanocarbon%20have%20made%20it%20to%20the%20domestic%20market%20in%20Delhi%2C%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%20and%20Pune%20in%20Maharasht